<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;bdi&gt;</code> (Bidirectional Isolate) element tells the browser's bidirectional algorithm to treat the text it contains in isolation from its surrounding text. This is particularly useful when embedding user-generated content or other text whose direction is unknown.</p>
    <p>Without <code>&lt;bdi&gt;</code>, a username in Arabic or Hebrew could cause the surrounding punctuation and text to display incorrectly due to the bidirectional algorithm treating it as part of a right-to-left sequence.</p>
  </section>

